title: A Drawing Editor for Stencil Design
title_en: A Drawing Editor for Stencil Design
abstract: 本研究はステンシル設計向けのドローイングエディタを提案し、ユーザの手描きデザインを印刷・切断可能なステンシル画像に変換する作業を扱っている。 本研究は正領域と負領域（positive／negative）を明示的に扱うインタラクティブな編集機能とブール演算に基づく領域生成、さらに切断用のSVG等の出力を通じて初心者でも簡便にステンシルを作成できることを目指している。
abstract_en: This work proposes a drawing editor for stencil design that converts users' hand-drawn designs into printable and cuttable stencil images. This work aims to provide interactive editing that explicitly handles positive/negative regions, uses boolean-based region generation, and outputs cuttable formats such as SVG to enable novices to create stencils easily.
positioning_summary: 本研究は既存の多機能な商用描画ツールや先行システムが初心者に扱いにくく、正領域・負領域の生成や切断用出力の作成が難しいというギャップを埋めることを位置づけている。 本研究はステンシル作成の文脈で、正露光／負露光（positive/negative）を効率的に取り扱える編集器の必要性を示している。
positioning_summary_en: This work positions itself as addressing the gap that existing multifunctional commercial drawing tools and prior systems are difficult for novices to use and make it hard to produce positive/negative regions and cut-output. This work highlights the need for an editor that efficiently handles positive/negative exposure in the context of stencil creation.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的は手描きデザインから実際に印刷・切断可能なステンシル画像を簡易に生成できる描画エディタを提供することである。 本研究はステンシル作成者や初心者ユーザを主な対象に、正領域と負領域の生成や印刷・切断用の出力を容易にする機能を実装することを目的としている。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this work is to provide a drawing editor that can easily generate printable and cuttable stencil images from hand-drawn designs. This work targets stencil creators and novice users and aims to implement features that simplify generating positive and negative regions and producing print/cut outputs.
method_summary: 本システムはユーザの手描きストロークを受けてバーチャルステンシル板上で編集を行い、ブール演算やpn系列に基づく要素合成で正領域と負領域を生成する描画エディタである。 本システムはストロークのグルーピングや生成されたブリッジを用し、ラスタ化＋フラッドフィルやSVG/DXF等への出力を含むワークフローで切断可能なステンシル画像を生成する仕組みを提供している。
method_summary_en: The system accepts users' hand-drawn strokes and performs editing on a virtual stencil board, generating positive and negative regions via boolean operations and element synthesis based on pn sequences. The system uses stroke grouping and generated bridges and provides a workflow including rasterization with flood fill and output to formats such as SVG/DXF to produce cuttable stencil images.
evaluation_summary: 本研究の評価は複数の比較実験と処理時間計測を組み合わせた方法で実施された。 本研究の比較実験では図中の変種比較で計66件がポジティブな評価を得ており、処理時間は1.1 GHz相当のPC上で典型的な形状処理で約5–10秒、複雑なケースで最大約10秒であった。
evaluation_summary_en: The evaluation in this work combined multiple comparative experiments and processing time measurements. In this work, the comparative experiments produced 66 positive evaluations in variant comparisons shown in figures, and processing times on a 1.1 GHz equivalent PC were about 5–10 seconds for typical shape processing and up to about 10 seconds for complex cases.

Title: A Drawing Editor for Stencil Design

Abstract: This work proposes a drawing editor for stencil design that converts users' hand-drawn designs into printable and cuttable stencil images. This work aims to provide interactive editing that explicitly handles positive/negative regions, uses boolean-based region generation, and outputs cuttable formats such as SVG to enable novices to create stencils easily.
Positioning Summary: This work positions itself as addressing the gap that existing multifunctional commercial drawing tools and prior systems are difficult for novices to use and make it hard to produce positive/negative regions and cut-output. This work highlights the need for an editor that efficiently handles positive/negative exposure in the context of stencil creation.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this work is to provide a drawing editor that can easily generate printable and cuttable stencil images from hand-drawn designs. This work targets stencil creators and novice users and aims to implement features that simplify generating positive and negative regions and producing print/cut outputs.
Method Summary: The system accepts users' hand-drawn strokes and performs editing on a virtual stencil board, generating positive and negative regions via boolean operations and element synthesis based on pn sequences. The system uses stroke grouping and generated bridges and provides a workflow including rasterization with flood fill and output to formats such as SVG/DXF to produce cuttable stencil images.
Evaluation Summary: The evaluation in this work combined multiple comparative experiments and processing time measurements.
